comment_regular_data.body:
> Oh I see, semirange doesn't seem to be implemented yet.

yes it's follow-up.

> Whereas the Ex equivalent :/license/,/shall/delete throws the "backwards range" warning.
And if accepted removes lines 70-74, which contain the next matches for shall and license respectively.
That seems intuitively correct to me.

> Maybe a "swap_on_backwards" bool is needed to be able to choose between the accept or cancel choice of the Ex equivalent.


yep .there is no interaction with the this API now.  for this `ex` case support is also easy. something like 
```
Boolean swap_range;  // auto-swap backward ranges (like answering 'y')

if (cmd->swap_range && ea.line1 > ea.line2) {
    linenr_T tmp = ea.line1;
    ea.line1 = ea.line2;
    ea.line2 = tmp;
}
...
```
